Q. I have several KRZ files named "name.kr1" up to "name.kr4", but Convert
give me an error, what happens?

A. Kurzweil samplers divide files larger than 1 disquette into several pieces.
Probably, "name.kr?" is a piece of a great file. Before using Convert, you have
to reasemble all pieces into a file. This can be done using JOIN, a utility 
supplied with Convert: JOIN name.krz will create a file called "name.krz" from
"name.kr1", "name.kr2"...

