Q. I agree with the Bidirectional to Forward Looping conversion but I want 
convert my bidirectional looped wavesample without looping, how can I do it?

A. Convert has an useful way to use bidirectional looped wavesamples with
formats which have only forward loop. This is made by increasing the wavesample
size and this can be no desirable. Then you can use the "-b" switch, which
maintains the original wavesample size and loop points, but lost the perfect
loop, in order to change to forward.

