Q. I agree with the Stereo to SBK conversion but I want to convert my stereo
wavesample to SBK in mono, how can I do it?

A. Convert uses multilayering to work with stereo wavesamples. This is made
using the left channel and the right channel as two layers with differents
panning positions (0 and 127). This can be avoided if you specify the "-1"
switch (the standard force mono switch).

